the function in Lua_web_socket.cpp  tolua_Cocos2d_WebSocket_sendString00:

```
    LuaWebSocket* self    = (LuaWebSocket*)  tolua_tousertype(tolua_S,1,0);
    size_t size = 0;
    const char* data = (const char*) lua_tolstring(tolua_S, 2, &size);
    if ( NULL == data)
        return 0;

    if (strlen(data) != size)
    {
        self->send((const unsigned char*)data, (unsigned int)size);
    }
    else
    {
        self->send(data);
    }
```

it's strange, you have already know the size of the string, you should just  self->send the string and the size. Why are you judging the size and auto judge to send as binary or text? 
this add the receiver's work!
I think If you want to supply two mode of send, you may add a parameter to let the sender to decide whether the string is text or binary.

On web platform browser support cookie automatic, but on device developer must manager cookie for websocket by modify onSocketCallback method of WebSocket class as below:

```
case LWS_CALLBACK_CLIENT_APPEND_HANDSHAKE_HEADER:
{
    if (!_cookie.empty()) {
        char **p = (char **)in;
        if (len < 100)
            return 1;

        *p += sprintf(*p, "Cookie: %s\x0d\x0a", _cookie.c_str());
        return 0;
    }
 }
 break;
```

Please support cookie for WebSocket, thank you very much!
